  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Project Scope**\n\nI\'m solidifying the core features for this data entry app. My current focus is on clearly defining the receipt parameters: amount, vendor, date, and category. I\'m also planning the database export to Postgres on Supabase and generating monthly spending reports.\n\n\n**Refining User Interface**\n\nI\'m now integrating a clean, dashboard-style interface for the spending reports. Text-based data input is the initial approach. It\'s crucial I don\'t enable Cloud SQL. Also, I\'m incorporating the \"Bento Grid\" design theme per the provided template. I\'m focusing on seamless Supabase integration using environment variables, specifically `SUPABASE_URL`, to avoid generating UI for API keys unless requested.\n\n\n**Considering Package Dependencies**\n\nI\'m now investigating package dependencies, specifically for Recharts and @supabase/supabase-js. I\'m noting potential import warnings, but Recharts\' ease of use is compelling. I will install both packages via install_applet_package, aiming for seamless integration. I\'ll watch for any issues arising from dependencies like d3, though.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Package Installations**\n\nI\'m now focusing on package installations. I\'m going with `@supabase/supabase-js` first, for real requests, if the user provides Supabase credentials. While I considered `recharts`, I\'m pivoting to crafting custom, interactive SVG charts using Tailwind CSS. This approach eliminates potential React 19 compatibility headaches and offers complete control over the visual presentation.\n\n\n\n**Evaluating Supabase Integration**\n\nI\'m now determining the integration of Supabase. The plan is using `@supabase/supabase-js` client-side, exposing the anon key. My goal is to follow Supabase best practices in a full-stack, client-side setup. Considering the constraints, I will create server-side API routes (`/api/*`) to proxy requests to maintain API key security.\n\n\n**Securing API Keys**\n\nI\'m now establishing secure API key handling. I\'ve realized that creating server-side API routes (`/api/*`) to proxy requests is essential for API key security, aligning with Supabase\'s best practices. I\'m going full-stack, creating a custom Express server (`server.ts`) to handle fetching, adding, and syncing receipts with Supabase, completely hiding the API key. I\'ll store receipts locally on the server (JSON, SQLite, or a variable) for persistence and stability, before exporting to Postgres.\n\n\n**Implementing Local Storage**\n\nI\'m now implementing local storage, which will ensure the application functions immediately without Supabase configuration. I\'m prioritizing localstorage-backed data persistence, with server-side storage (memory/JSON) as a fallback. I\'ll synchronize data with Supabase if the user provides the environment variables, ensuring symmetrical syncing. This approach ensures a crash-proof application that functions seamlessly.\n\n\n**Designing the Interface**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in the UI design, aiming for a Bento Grid layout for the main view. I\'m planning for toggle tabs (Dashboard, Receipt History, Custom Reports) within this layout, ensuring a single-page app structure. I\'m focusing on the sidebar, which will contain the LedgerFlow logo, navigation with active/inactive states, and a Supabase connection status card. I\'ll implement responsive and interactive elements. I\'m also planning the header with \"Financial Overview \342\200\224 October\", Export CSV, and Sync Postgres buttons, including the required CSV export and Postgres sync functionality. Summary cards will display Total Spending, Receipts, and the Top Category, while a Bento cell will house the Quick Entry form with fields for vendor, amount, date, and category.\n\n\n**Constructing Chart Component**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in developing a custom, interactive SVG charting component. My focus is on crafting a dynamic visual representation of month-by-month spending or category breakdowns, complete with interactive tooltips. I\'m eliminating chart libraries that can create runtime issues. I\'ll also integrate a Recent Transactions Table, showing entries with category tags, sync status, and amounts. I\'ll support receipt deletion, editing/re-syncing, and month/category filtering. I\'ll check `package.json` for installations.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will begin by inspecting the initial `package.json` file to check the scripts and see if `@supabase/supabase-js` needs to be installed, after which I will proceed with installing any necessary dependencies."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 14
