    thinking: "**Designing the Server**\n\nOkay, I\'m working on the `server.ts` design. My immediate focus is establishing the core functionality. I\'ve decided, for robustness, to store local receipts in memory, at least for now. I\'m prioritizing efficient local receipt management.\n\n\n**Considering Persistence Options**\n\nI\'ve shifted focus to data persistence. Now, I\'m leaning toward using `./receipts.json` in the workspace root for its persistent nature. I am reviewing the data structure now and determining the fields I will need for each receipt. I need to consider fields like ID, amount, vendor, date, category, status, and creation timestamp.\n\n\n**Integrating with Supabase**\n\nI\'m now integrating with Supabase. My plan is to export vendor, date, and category data and generate monthly reports. Initially, I\'ll focus on text input. I\'ll need a Supabase table setup, so I\'ll generate a SQL script for table creation. I\'ll also check for Supabase credentials in the environment and push pending receipts to Supabase if the environment variables are set.\n\n\n**Implementing Database Sync**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the database sync functionality. I\'m planning a simple `supabase.from(\'receipts\').insert([...])` under the hood. Upon a successful insert, I will update the receipt status to \'synced\'. Clear error messages are essential, I\'ll provide detailed feedback to the user regarding authorization or table failures, for example, missing table details. I\'m also planning a \"Database Sync\" card on the sidebar with clear visual indicators for connected, partially configured, or not configured states. A `/api/db-status` endpoint will handle the sync status checks.\n\n\n**Initializing Local Receipts**\n\nI am now focusing on the initial setup of local receipts. I will create `./receipts.json` if it doesn\'t exist, initializing it with a few pre-loaded, styled template receipts. This will give users an immediately functional dashboard on first launch, showcasing the analytics. These template receipts will be from recent weeks like June and May 2026. This setup should ensure a great first user experience.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now create the backend entry point `server.ts` using Express. It will handle local persistence in a JSON store (`receipts.json`), expose API routes to manage receipts, perform actual synchronization with the external Supabase Postgres database if credentials are set, and integrate Vite as middleware during development."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 8
      nanos: 915906534
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
